  02 Nov 2005; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  Added license checking.

  01 Nov 2005; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  Fixed installation when not using USE=nowin.

  17 Oct 2005; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  Added nwmouse check from bug #106789 for bug #109619.

  30 Sep 2005; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  Fixed cosmetic errors on USE=-nowin.

  22 Sep 2005; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  Added echo lines to inform users which CD they'll need.

*nwn-data-1.29 (21 Sep 2005)

  21 Sep 2005; Chris Gianelloni <wolf31o2@gentoo.org> +files/nwn.png,
  +metadata.xml, +nwn-data-1.29.ebuild:
  Initial import. Ebuild by me. This is the first ebuild for breaking up
  Neverwinter Nights into 2 ebuilds. This ebuild also adds support for
  installing the Shadows of Undrentide and Hordes of the Underdark expansion
  packs from CD using USE=sou and USE=hou respectively.

